SIMPLE: overshot
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overshot
<hw>O"ver*shot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>From
<er>Overshoot</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Overshot wheel</b></col>, <cd>a vertical water wheel, the
circumference of which is covered with cavities or buckets, and which is
turned by water which shoots over the top of it, filling the buckets on
the farther side and acting chiefly by its weight.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overshot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overshot
<hw>O"ver*shot`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the
upper teeth projecting beyond the lower; -- said of the jaws of some
dogs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oversight</ent>⟦br⟧
